/*
______________________________________________________(F.E.E.D.)____
-----------------------------(feedly_extended_experience_display)---

Design and code by Odysseas Kourafalos - aka Ducklord
An Uncensored|Media (uncensored.gr)creation for unregistered.gr

PLEASE, READ THE FOLLOWING UPDATE MESSAGE, or you may start wondering
where the heck your Feedly's menu has gone!


0.76 UPDATE: another change by Feedly, another fix by me.
Specifically, Feedly updated the way it displays its sidebar, so,
I changed the way the main article area "behaves". Now when you
hover over it with your mouse, it covers most of the screen. When
you move your mouse to the left, it "slides" to the right to reveal
the main menu.



Hope you like the changes and additions.
As always, I'm open to ideas and recomentations.

Best regards,
Odysseas Kourafalos
aka Ducklord

http://unregistered.gr
http://uncensored.gr



_____________________________________( IN PREVIOUS EPISODES...)_____

0.75 UPDATE: Fixes main area that was a bit screwey after Feedlys
latest upgrades. Just one CSS rule changed.

--------------------------------------------------------------------

0.73 UPDATE: fixed to work with the latest version of Feedly where
you can "pin/unpin" the menu bar on the left. It DOESN'T work 100%
correctly, as when you "pin" the bar, you lose some pixels (about
300) from the content area. Use it unpinned until I find some time
to bypass Feedlys new rules. Maybe it's time for a total redesign..!

--------------------------------------------------------------------


0.72 UPDATE: Just some margin-padding fixes.
Well, feast your eyes on animated zoom scaling for easier reading, a
different style (and tweaked logic) in posts images (now, they move,
"to show a different part of them" - since our compact size means I
had to cut part of them). And since I've added the scaling effect, I
thought "what the heck" and added a drop shadow as a bonus, so as to
better seperate the selected post from the rest.

If only Feedly's team had used some more defining IDs and classes in
their HTML code, as well as a bit less restricted structure... Ah,
the places we would go...

Anyways, I hope you like the update.


FUNTIME: Just for the heck of it, with F.E.E.D. applied, try disabling
the style in Stylish. We've gone a loooong way from the default style!

--------------------------------------------------------------------


Version: 0.62

My my! Post display radically changed in Magazine View. Check it
out!



--------------------------------------------------------------------

Version: 0.61

Changes and stuff:

Fixed the "fourth blank recommended post" by forcing the
re-styling of ONLY the three first "boxes" in Feedly's "Recommended"
area. This is a nasty hack, since if Feedly decides someday to show
more than three posts, the rest will be hidden.

Ah, well... We can't have it all, can we? :-D

Apart from that:

Fixed "recommended" image size to be full width.

Added bit of code that alows "recommended" image to show a little bit
more when user hovers over its post. At the same time, I've added a
bit of movement - a change in "point of interest" - in every image
to the top, so as to, again, show a little bit more - this time,
through the very movement, by showing the user a different part of
the whole image. Thus, we keep both our nice, clean and compact view,
and see more of each post.

The big change comes in how normal post images (and normal posts in
general) are displayed. They may look the same to you, until you
hover over one. Surprise! :-D

Lastly, I've added this portion to the script. Now, that's what I'd
call "a mindblowing new feature"... :-D



__ UPDATE v0.5 __
Strangely, Feedly didn't display "recommended posts" lately for me, preventing me from styling them. Now, the problem is (partially) fixed (well, they don't look their best, but it works).
While fixing this, I tweaked and balanced better the spacing between the cards in Magazine View, for an even better, more compact display.

__ UPDATE v0.4 __
Fixed erratic behavior in List view (no more strange spacing between articles - I hope). Restricted "source" width to gain space for article title, and made it disappear when under 1200px window size - leaving the whole available space for post titles. Also added the "opacity" effect to this mode as well, when hovering over an article. Yeah, noticed the problems only minutes after my last update, so, I guess, THIS will be the last one for awhile. :-)

__ UPDATE v0.3 __
Version 0.3 fixed for lower resolutions. Responsive design logic, with different article-box analogies according to screen resolution. Bonus, an opacity change when you hover your mouse over an article, "solidifying" it as "pure white". I guess that'll be the final version for awhile, until I find any problems or decide to tackle the rest of Feedlys different methods of displaying articles.


__ UPDATE v0.2 __

Version 0.2 REMOVES grouping from Magazine View and emulates Feedlys original Cards View. But, of course, in a vastly upgraded, compact way, that uses every inch of space of your monitor. So, if you like the grouping feature (which, I must confess, doesn't work too well with my slow-as-heck connection and Feedlys "streaming" way of loading articles), stick with the previous one.

The reason for changing from wide tiles to cards? Better view of images and more space for the "actions" of Feedly (Save / Mark as read), that were "cut" in many cases with F.E.E.D.s first version.

I'm open to ideas and requests for improving F.E.E.D. even more. As I've already said, in my case it changed the way I read news, helping me speed through hundreds of posts in minutes. I hope you find it useful as well.

If you like it, pass the word around, help others... "see the light" as well. That way, maybe Feedlys team themselves may change their silly design that constricts their service to half our full HD widescreens. And maybe borrow some ideas of mine! :-D

-------------------------------------------------------------------- 
*/

